URL:

👉️ window.location   ->  gives info on the current location
👉️ window.location.href="somurl"  -> sends to "someurl"

👉️ window.location.search -> returns the url without the host i.e if url ="http://localhost:7000?query=abc, 
																it returns ?query=abc
👉️ URLSearchParams:

 const urlparams = new URLSearchParams(input)
 if input = http://locahost:7000?foo=bar&baz=qux
	output = { 'foo' => 'bar', 'baz' => 'qux' }
	--> use to extract query in frontend. urlparams.get("foo")
if input = {foo: "bar" , baz : "qux }
	output = { 'foo' => 'bar', 'baz' => 'qux' }
	--> use to create query to attach to a url in backend.
	
👉️
